      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027m not familar with \"current draw\" or saveLayer(), can you explain a bit how those would work for filter inputs?\n\nTwo ways to apply an image filter: via a draw paint drawFoo(..., IMF) or via a layer paint saveLayer(..., IMF).\n\nA nullptr filter input refers to the \"current draw\" content - either the explicit layer or an implicit layer generated with drawFoo\u0027s content.  This is equivalent to SourceGraphic, and it means you don\u0027t really have to package the input in a separate SkPicture.\n\nE.g. if you wanted to filter a drawCircle you could do this https://fiddle.skia.org/c/6aa41a12d4fcfc0c47f824d6967b89ba\n\nFor arbitrary content (not necessarily an atomic draw) the process is usually\n\n1) saveLayer(IMF)\n2) draw content\n3) restore\n\nwhere nullptr in the filter DAG is essentially the layer content/sourcegraphic: https://fiddle.skia.org/c/3afa417d130607693ec51f5af4c1e345",
